info.kuechler.bmf.taxcalculator

Class AccessorImpl<T extends Calculator<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • info.kuechler.bmf.taxcalculator.AccessorImpl<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the Calculator implementation
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Accessor<String,T>

    public class AccessorImpl<T extends Calculator<T>>
extends Object
implements Accessor<String,T>
    Implementation of Accessor. To handle case insensitive keys use createValueMap() for parameter Maps for constructor.
    Since:
    2018.0.0

      • set

        public <V> void set(String key,
                    V value)
        Set a value. The value will be convert into BigDecimal, int or double.

        Be sure that you are already using the correct type or choose a type so that the value can be converted without loss. For correct target type see Accessor.getInputsWithType().

        Conversion
        Target Type Source Type Conversion
        int Number Number.intValue()
        double Number Number.doubleValue()
        BigDecimal BigDecimal -
        BigInteger BigInteger bi = (BigInteger) value;
        new BigDecimal(bi)
        Integer
        Byte
        Short
        AtomicInteger        		 int i = ((Number) value).intValue();
        new BigDecimal(i);
        Long
        AtomicLong        		 long l = ((Number) value).longValue();
        new BigDecimal(l);
        Double
        Float        		 double d = ((Number) value).doubleValue();
        new BigDecimal(d);
        another Number object throws IllegalArgumentException
        ... not Number throws IllegalArgumentException
